 Their names are as follows:--Succoot, Machass, Dongola, Shageia, Monasier, Isyout, Rab-a-Tab, Berber, Shendi, Halfya, the kingdoms of Sennaar, Darfour, and Kordofan\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 
; at present, all subject to the conqueror of Egypt and Arabia.
\par }}}{\f0\insrsid11228189\charrsid16408944 \hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0  are not the only consequences of this expedition that will give him glory.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 This expedition has l\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 
aid open to the researches of the geographer and the antiquarian a river and a country highly interesting, and hitherto imperfectly known to the civilized world. The Nile, on whose banks we have marched for so many hundred miles, is the most famous river 
\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 
n the world, for the uncertainty of its source and the obscurity of its course. At present this obscurity ceases to exist, and before the return of the Pasha Ismael this uncertainty will probably be no more.  The countries we have traversed are renowned i
\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 
 history and poetry as the land of ancient and famous nations, which have established and overthrown mighty empires, and have originated the religions, the learning, the arts, and the civilization of nations long since extinct; and who have been preceded 
\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 b\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 y their instructors in the common road which every thing human must travel.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 This famous land of Cush and Saba, at present overawed by the camps of the Osmanii, has presented to our observation many memorials of the power and splendor of its ancient master\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 
s. The remains of cities once populous--ruined temples once magnificent--colossal statues of idols once adored, but now prostrated by the strong arms of time and truth--and more than a hundred pyramids, which entomb the bodies of kings and conquerors once
\hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af36\loch\f0 
mighty, but whose memory has perished, have suspended for awhile the march of our troops--have attracted the notice of the Franks, who voyage with the army with the favor and the protection of the Pasha,}{\cs16\f0\super\insrsid11228189\charrsid16408944 
\chftn {\footnote \pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16408944 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af36\hich\af36\dbch\af36\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
